tor to create B from A.Otherwise, if A is a class type you can modify, use an overloaded typecast to convert A to B.Otherwise use a non-member function to convert A to B.Next lesson21.12Overloading the assignment operatorBack to table of contentsPrevious lesson21.10Overloading the parenthesis operator

Take a look at the following class:class Cents
